[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "513dd00ede743f380af2152958b4289ab9e18af9baa1dbf78b645929250f3c41"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/basic_bidding"]
[Student "S"]
{EAST has an above-minimum strength hand with a good 6-card suit. He opens 1\H.

WEST, with 9 points, is a little too weak to bid at the 2-level so she bids a catchall 1NT.

EAST shows his 6-card suit and extra strength by jumping to 3\H, which 
WEST raises to 4\H since two trumps is now adequate support.}

